BOOT.ASM is the basic boot sector.
TRIVBOOT.ASM is the trivial boot sector virus.
KILROY.ASM is the Kilroy-B virus.

All may be assembled with MASM, TASM or A86 to a COM file, and then loaded
onto a floppy disk.

BOOTREAD.EXE reads a boot sector from the A: drive into a file named BOOT.SEC.
BOOTWRT.EXE writes the boot sector in BOOT.SEC into the boot sector on A:
